# .git-wt-copy-files
#
# When you run `git-wt new <branch>`, git-wt copies the files matching these
# patterns from the main repo into the new worktree. Copy this file to
# `.git-wt-copy-files` (without the .example extension) at the repo root and
# commit it so your team shares the same setup.
#
# Format
#   - one pattern per line
#   - blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored
#   - patterns are matched at the top level of the repo (no `**` recursion)
#   - glob characters: *, ?, [...]
#   - `!pattern` excludes matches (applied after includes)
#   - trailing `/` is ignored (you can write it for clarity)
#
# When this file is absent, git-wt falls back to the built-in defaults below.

# Local-only env files
.env
.env.*

# Claude / AI tooling configuration
.claude/
CLAUDE.local.md
.ai-cache/

# Examples — uncomment to opt in
# .vscode/settings.json
# .idea/
# docker-compose.override.yml

# Examples of exclusions — applied after the includes above
# !.env.production
# !.env.secrets
